@NODE Allgemeines "Allgemeines"

 DESCRIPTION
 -----------
 This Module creates ImageGadgets. It contains 3 GetFile-Gadgets,
 and you can create your own gadgets with your own images.


 SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
 -------------------

 Kickstart 2.04+
 Workbench 2.0 OR Workbench 2.1 for localized texts


@ENDNODE

@NODE Funktionen "Programmieranleitung"

 I simply create GadToolsGadgets of type GENERIC_KIND. Then the
 gadget structure will be filled.


 In the Module are declared:
  - g: PTR TO gadget -> used as PTR to gadgetlist
  - visual           -> the VisualInfo for GadTools

 You MUST use this variables in your window, or the Guru will come!!!


 @{" Example: imagedemo.e "}

@ENDNODE

@NODE F1 "ImageGadgets V1.0"

 @{" gcc_InitImageGadgets() "}

 Inputs:  NONE
 Outputs: NONE

 Purpose:
 Activates the internal securitychecks. This function is only meaningful,
 if you use the internal images of this module.

 ATTENTION!!!
 If you use this function, it MUST be the first function used from this
 module!! 


 Index: @{" gcc_InitDiskImage()     " LINK F2}
        @{" gcc_RemoveDiskImage(nr) " LINK F3}


@ENDNODE

@NODE F2 "ImageGadgets V1.0"

 @{" gcc_InitDiskImage(nr,modus) "}

 Inputs:  # nr = type of internal gadget
            0 - GadToolsBox (20x14x3)
            1 - small Disk  (30x15x3)
            2 - medium Disk (30x17x3)

          # modus = background
            0 - no background
            1 - color 3 (blue)

 Outputs: NONE

 Purpose:
 Inits the image for the type of gadget. You MUST use this function BEFORE
 you can create a gadget with @{" gcc_CreateGetFileA() " LINK F4}! 


 Index: @{" gcc_InitImageGadgets()  " LINK F1}
        @{" gcc_RemoveDiskImage(nr) " LINK F3}


@ENDNODE

@NODE F3 "ImageGadgets V1.0"

 @{" gcc_RemoveDiskImage(nr) "}

 Inputs:  # nr = type of internal gadget
            0..2 - number of type
            ALL  - all images

 Outputs: NONE

 Purpose:
 Frees the image and the used chip ram.

 ATTENTION!!!
 Don't free a images, which is not installed! If the internal securitycheck
 is not activated, you can see the Guru.


 Index: @{" gcc_InitImageGadgets()  " LINK F1}
        @{" gcc_InitDiskImage()     " LINK F2}


@ENDNODE

@NODE F4 "ImageGadgets V1.0"

 @{" gcc_CreateGetFileA(nr,x,y,flagstatus) "}

 Inputs:  # nr = type of internal gadget
            0 - GadToolsBox  (20x14x3)
            1 - small Disk   (30x15x3)
            2 - medium Disk  (30x17x3)

          # x,y = coordinate of gadget

          # flagstatus = mode of gadget
            0 - enabled
            1 - disabled

 Outputs: PTR TO gadget or -1

 Purpose:
 Creates a GetFile-Gadget.

 ATTENTION!!!
 The image for this type must be installed BEFORE with @{" gcc_InitDiskImage() " LINK F2}.


 Index: @{" gcc_InitImageGadgets()  " LINK F1}
        @{" gcc_RemoveDiskImage(nr) " LINK F3}


@ENDNODE

@NODE F5 "ImageGadgets V1.0"

 @{" gcc_InstallGetFileA(nr,x,y,modus,flagstatus) "}

 Inputs:  # nr = type of internal gadget
            0 - GadToolsBox  (20x14x3)
            1 - small Disk   (30x15x3)
            2 - medium Disk  (30x17x3)

          # x,y = coordinate of gadget

          # modus = background
            0 - no background
            1 - color 3 (blue)

          # flagstatus = mode of gadget
            0 - enabled
            1 - disabled

 Outputs: PTR TO gadget or -1

 Purpose:
 Inits and creates a Getfile-Gadget. The image for this gadget type is
 installed, and you can create gadgets of the same type with @{" gcc_CreateGetFileA() " LINK F4}.


 Index: @{" gcc_RemoveDiskImage(nr) " LINK F3}


@ENDNODE

@NODE F6 "ImageGadgets V1.0"

 @{" gcc_CreateGadgetA(x,y,n1: PTR TO image,n2: PTR TO image,flagstatus) "}

 Inputs:  # x,y = coordinate of gadget

          # n1,n2 = PTR TO image
              n1 - normal
              n2 - selected (PTR TO image or NIL)

          # flagstatus = mode of gadget
            0 - enabled
            1 - disabled

 Outputs: PTR TO gadget or -1

 Purpose:
 Creates a ImageGadget. Width and height are same values as in the image.
 The gadgets are of the type BUTTON.


 Index: @{" gcc_SetGadgetAttrsA() " LINK F7}


@ENDNODE

@NODE F7 "ImageGadgets V1.0"

 @{" gcc_SetGadgetAttrsA(name,win:PTR TO window,befehl,stat) "}

 Inputs:  # name = name of the gadget

          # win = PTR to the Window with the gadget

          # befehl = gadget flag to change
            GA_DISABLED - enable or disable the gadget

          # stat = stat of the gadget flag
            0 - ON
            1 - OFF

 Outputs: NONE

 Purpose:
 Changes a attributes of the gadget.

 ATTENTION!!!
 The created gadgets are real GadToolsGadgets, but of GENERIC_KIND.
 You can't change this kind of gadget with GT_SetGadgetAttrsA().
 Therefore you have to use this function to change a ImageGadget.


 Index: @{" gcc_CreateGadgetA() " LINK F6}


@ENDNODE

